[2] Sierra Leone lockdown extended
Date: Sun 4 Jan 2015
Source: Yahoo News, AFP (Agence France-Presse) report [edited]
http://news.yahoo.com/ebola-lockdown-sierra-leone-airport-checks-upped-191625879.html


New Ebola lockdown in Sierra Leone as airport checks upped
----------------------------------------------------------
The Ebola lockdown in the northern Tonkolili district of Sierra Leone was extended on Sun [4 Jan 2015] for 2 weeks as authorities stepped up the fight to contain the epidemic. The move comes as the government imposed "additional screening measures" at Freetown International Airport after 2 workers apparently caught the disease [confirmed by laboratory testing on 2 Jan 2015].

A 5-day lockdown had been declared by the government across the badly-hit north of the country last month [December 2014]. "The lockdown is extended for another 2 weeks to intensify monitoring efforts by all sectors in the district as we need this mopping up operation until 17 Jan [2015]," he added.

