[4] Liberia: 9 counties Ebola-free
Date: Mon 5 Jan 2015
Source: Star Africa [edited]
http://en.starafrica.com/news/nine-counties-in-liberia-report-no-new-ebola-cases-for-over-21-days-un.html


9 counties in Liberia report no new Ebola cases for over 21 days -- UN
----------------------------------------------------------------------
According to [Hans] Rosling, [an official of the United Nations Mission on Ebola Emergency Response (UNMEER)], Grand Gedeh, River Gee, Grand Kru, Maryland and Rivercess counties in south-eastern Liberia, Grand Bassa County in eastern Liberia, as well as Gbarpolu and Bomi counties have reported no confirmed cases of the Ebola Virus Disease (EVD) for more than 21 days, while Lofa County in northern Liberia has reported 0 cases in more than 40 days. Foya in Lofa County registered Liberia's 1st case of Ebola in early March 2014, with the disease subsequently spreading to other parts of the country.

At the same time, according to Rosling, 6 counties: Cape Mount, Montserrado, Bong, Nimba, Margibi and Sinoe, have reported just over 70 Ebola cases in the last 3 weeks.

The World Health Organization (WHO) will declare a country Ebola-free if it does not record any new Ebola case in 42 days.

--
Communicated by:
ProMED-mail
<promed@promedmail.org>

[This good news does not mean support should be withdrawn from the country. See http://www.cbsnews.com/news/sen-coons-calls-for-change-in-u-s-ebola-strategy Face the Nation interview with Senator Chris Coons, 4 Jan 2015, discussing why USA should change strategy in Liberia using funding to help insure Liberians can develop and sustain local health facilities from the emergency Ebola treatment centres. - Mod.LK]

